item: A job for a veteran is more than a source of income. It is a new mission, with a new status, and the transition can be difficult. It is a national scandal that veterans are one of the groups with the highest unemployment rates.

item: The same thing is true of a similar limitation on the importation of tobacco. In such a community there is no farming or middle class tending to build up a conservative, self-respecting community, capable of self-government. There are many other products, notably that of Manila hemp, to which the energy of the islands can be, and is being, directed, the cultivation of which develops the class of small and intelligent farmers.

item: Those who preside over the worst energy shortage in our history tell us to use less, so that we will run out of oil, gasoline, and natural gas a little more slowly. Conservation is desirable, of course, for we must not waste energy. But conservation is not the sole answer to our energy needs.

item: To do this right, we must truly internationalize both politically and militarily: we cannot depend on a US-only presence.

item: To our allies let us send from this convention one message from our hearts: The American people are united with you to the limit of our resources and manpower, devoted to the single task of victory and the establishment of a firm and lasting peace.

extract: ['The American people stand united with you, our allies, in our pursuit of victory and the establishment of lasting peace.', 'We are committed to supporting our allies in their endeavors to achieve victory and build a better future.', 'The American people are our partners in the pursuit of freedom and democracy, and we will do everything in our power to help them achieve their goals.', 'We are proud to stand with our allies and to work together to build a more peaceful and prosperous world.', 'The American people are a force to be reckoned with, and we will do everything in our power to ensure that they achieve their full potential.']

item: We all know how truly the world has become one- that if Germany and Japan, for example, were to come through this war with their philosophies established and their armies intact, our own grandchildren would again have to be fighting in their day for their liberties and their lives.
paraphrase_0: {   "language": "English",   "paraphrases": [     "If Germany and Japan were to face a war with their established philosophies and intact armies, our grandchildren would be forced to fight for their liberties and lives in the present day." ,     "The legacy of war and the struggle for freedom would be passed down to future generations, even if Germany and Japan emerged victorious." ,     "The sacrifices of past generations would be meaningless if the world were to witness a similar war between Germany and Japan." ,     "The horrors of war would be repeated, and the pursuit of freedom would be an uphill battle." ,     "The legacy of war would be a constant reminder of the human cost of conflict."   ] }
extract: ['If Germany and Japan were to face a war with their established philosophies and intact armies, our grandchildren would be forced to fight for their liberties and lives in the present day.', 'The legacy of war and the struggle for freedom would be passed down to future generations, even if Germany and Japan emerged victorious.', 'The sacrifices of past generations would be meaningless if the world were to witness a similar war between Germany and Japan.', 'The horrors of war would be repeated, and the pursuit of freedom would be an uphill battle.', 'The legacy of war would be a constant reminder of the human cost of conflict.']

item: We are the party that trusts in the people. I trust in the people. That is the heart of all I have tried to say tonight.

item: We believe that now that the world looks more like America, it's time for America to look more like herself. And so we offer a philosophy that puts faith in the individual, not the bureaucracy; a philosophy that empowers people to do their best, so America can be at its best. In a world that is safer and freer, this is how we will build an America that is stronger, safer, and more secure.
paraphrase_0: {   "language": "English",   "paraphrases": [     "We believe that now that the world looks more like America, it's time for America to reflect its own values and aspirations.",     "We propose a philosophy that prioritizes individual empowerment and freedom, enabling individuals to reach their full potential.",     "By fostering a sense of safety and freedom, we can unlock the immense potential of the American spirit.",     "We envision a future where America is a beacon of hope and prosperity for the world, built on the principles of individual liberty and equality.",     "A world where America stands as a symbol of strength, security, and resilience, a testament to the enduring spirit of its people."   ] }

item: We have been neutral not only because it was the fixed and traditional policy of the United States to stand aloof from the politics of Europe and because we had had no part either of action or of policy in the influences which brought on the present war, but also because it was manifestly our duty to prevent, if it were possible, the indefinite extension of the fires of hate and desolation kindled by that terrible conflict and seek to serve mankind by reserving cur strength and our resources for the anxious and difficult days of restoration and healing which must follow, when peace will have to build its house anew.
paraphrase_0: {   "language": "English",   "paraphrases": [     "We have remained neutral out of a sense of duty and a commitment to preventing the further escalation of violence and destruction."     "We have been neutral because we had no role to play in the events that led to the current conflict and because we were committed to protecting human life and promoting peace."     "We have been neutral because we recognized that it was our responsibility to prevent the continuation of the cycle of hatred and suffering that had led to the war."     "We have been neutral because we understood that it was our duty to help those who were suffering and to work towards a better future."     "We have been neutral because we recognized that the war was a global conflict and that we needed to work together to find a solution."   ] }
extract: ['We have remained neutral out of a sense of duty and a commitment to preventing the further escalation of violence and destruction.', 'We have been neutral because we had no role to play in the events that led to the current conflict and because we were committed to protecting human life and promoting peace.', 'We have been neutral because we recognized that it was our responsibility to prevent the continuation of the cycle of hatred and suffering that had led to the war.', 'We have been neutral because we understood that it was our duty to help those who were suffering and to work towards a better future.', 'We have been neutral because we recognized that the war was a global conflict and that we needed to work together to find a solution.']

item: We need rebirth of the American tradition of leadership at every level of government and in private life as well. The United States of America is unique in world history because it has a genius for leaders--many leaders--on many levels. But, back in 1976, Mr. Carter said, Trust me. And a lot of people did. Now, many of those people are out of work. Many have seen their savings eaten away by inflation. Many others on fixed incomes, especially the elderly, have watched helplessly as the cruel tax of inflation wasted away their purchasing power. And, today, a great many who trusted Mr. Carter wonder if we can survive the Carter policies of national defense.
paraphrase_0: {   "language": "English",   "paraphrases": [     "The American tradition of leadership is in dire need of a revival at all levels of government and in private life.",     "The United States stands as a beacon of hope for the world, but its leadership has faltered in recent years.",     "The American people deserve to have their leaders work tirelessly to ensure that they have a fair shot at success.",     "The American dream is under threat from the rising cost of living and the erosion of purchasing power.",     "The American people deserve to have their leaders prioritize the needs of the people and work towards a better future."   ] }
extract: ['The American tradition of leadership is in dire need of a revival at all levels of government and in private life.', 'The United States stands as a beacon of hope for the world, but its leadership has faltered in recent years.', 'The American people deserve to have their leaders work tirelessly to ensure that they have a fair shot at success.', 'The American dream is under threat from the rising cost of living and the erosion of purchasing power.', 'The American people deserve to have their leaders prioritize the needs of the people and work towards a better future.']

item: We oppose wars and military interventions waged by the imperialist powers such as those of the Us, europe and russia in the Middle east and North africa in the last decade and a half.
paraphrase_0: {   "language": "English",   "paraphrases": [     "We strongly condemn the senseless and unnecessary wars waged by the powerful nations of the West in the Middle East and North Africa in the past decade and a half.",     "We believe that war is a violation of human rights and that it should never be used to achieve political goals.",     "We are deeply troubled by the human toll and the destruction caused by the wars in the Middle East and North Africa.",     "We urge all nations to work together to end the cycle of violence and to promote peace and stability in the region.",     "We call on the international community to hold the imperialist powers accountable for their actions and to ensure that they comply with international law."   ] }
extract: ['We strongly condemn the senseless and unnecessary wars waged by the powerful nations of the West in the Middle East and North Africa in the past decade and a half.', 'We believe that war is a violation of human rights and that it should never be used to achieve political goals.', 'We are deeply troubled by the human toll and the destruction caused by the wars in the Middle East and North Africa.', 'We urge all nations to work together to end the cycle of violence and to promote peace and stability in the region.', 'We call on the international community to hold the imperialist powers accountable for their actions and to ensure that they comply with international law.']

item: You and I have been working toward a more secure future by rebuilding our military strength—steadily, carefully, and responsibly. The Republicans talk about military strength, but they were in office for 8 out of the last 11 years, and in the face of a growing Soviet threat they steadily cut real defense spending by more than a third.
